cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper presents a method that uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for real-time 2D/3D registration. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of CNNs for regression also falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The method is applied to medical imaging, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
